text: Sherman Hall (May 11, 1885 - July 20, 1954) was an American fencer. He competed in three events at the 1912 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1885 births Category:1954 deaths Category:American male fencers Category:Olympic fencers of the United States Category:Fencers at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Cambridge, Massachusetts
